cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about Grammatical Error Correction (GEC) using a Transformer sequence-to-sequence model. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses training models on large amounts of weakly supervised bitext. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper describes an approach to GEC that uses machine learning techniques. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a potential category as the paper uses a neural network model for GEC. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses an iterative decoding strategy that is tailored to the loosely-supervised nature of the Wikipedia training corpus.
